{{Sangam literature}}
'''Nallanthuvanar''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: நல்லந்துவனார்), also known in full as Madurai Aasiriyar Nallanthuvanar ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: மதுரையாசிரியர் நல்லந்துவனார்), was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 39 verses of the Sangam literature has been attributed, in addition to verse 18 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages = 30–31 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Nallanthuvanar was born as "Anthuvan" and was known for his erudition in [[Tamil language]] and [[astronomy]]. He was praised by poet Madurai Marudhan Ilanaganar.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = குறுந்தொகை, பரிபாடல், கலித்தொகை [Kurunthogai, Paripadal, Kalitthogai] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 2 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 244–247 (Book II) | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Nallanthuvanar has written 39 Sangam verse, including 4 in [[Paripaadal]] (verses 6, 8, 11, and 20), 1 in [[Agananuru]] (verse 43), 1 in [[Natrinai]] (verse 88), and 33 in [[Kalithogai]], besides verse 18 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/> In addition to composing the Kalitthogai verses, he also compiled the work of Kalitthogai and wrote its invocation verse.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = அகநானூறு, புறநானூறு [Agananuru, Purananuru] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 3 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 249 (Book I) | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
